…Granted 25m bail  Suspended Director General (DG) of the Security and Exchange Commission (SEC), Mounir Haliru Gwarzo and Executive Commissioner, Corporate Services, Zakawaru Garuba have been arraigned before a High Court of the Federal Capital Territory (FCT) in Maitama, Abuja. They were arraigned on Tuesday on a five-count charge in which they were accused of misappropriating about N115million naira. Justice Hussein Baba-Yusuf granted them bail of N25m each with one surety, who must be a Deputy Director in any Federal Government ministries or agencies. The judge also said the sureties must own land within the FCT, while the defendants are to deposit their international passports with the court’ Registry. Details later…